My #visionboard is coming together nicely. .

I’ll be continuing to add to my board as I find images that will set the intention I want into the universe. .

I broke up my board into 5 quadrants. Travel, Health Relationship, Money and a huge fat goal for myself right in the center of my board. .

The hardest part was the relationship quadrant.  How long should I wait? What’s healthy?  Am I somehow dishonoring my husband?  Is this to soon?? .

I’ve been meditating a lot on this and the fact that I’m uncomfortable and don’t want to face this part of my life is EXACTLY why I have to. .

Now, please no lurkers thinking this is some kind of an “Open for Business” post.  I’m NOT interested in ANYONE.  I’m just focusing myself on developing the skill set I’ll need to even be open to the possibility! .

So seriously,  please don’t do me any favors by reaching out.  My fuse is as short as a rattlesnakes lately and I’d love nothing more than an excuse to thin out my friends list.

Absolutely disgusting. I am sending healing and love to all of those beautiful young girls. I’m so thankful you are getting the justice you deserve. Walid, please throughly enjoy your time in prison. You’ll get yours. 😡

“So you want to change the world? You want to be a leader? It’s not about what you can or can’t do. But what God can do through you. Satan knows that. So He will try to bring you down… not through failure or lack of success or lack of finances or resources but through sin. Sin takes up space in our lives and keeps us from from being filled with the light of Jesus. The darkness within us will crush us when the spotlight is on us. We need to be filled with His light. (1 John 1:7). Totally and completely filled so there is no room for darkness.

Sexual sin thrives in the dark. It feeds off the secret hidden corners of our heart. On Incognito web pages. Snap chats that erase. Instagram hashtags that we scroll through hoping to accidentally stumble across something that we know we shouldn’t see but secretly want to.

From the #metoo and the #churchtoo movement, leaders are being caught in sexual sin that has been hiding in the dark for decades.

The enemy has been bringing down leaders with sexual sin from the very beginning. 
Samson and Delilah (Judges 17), David and Bathsheba (2 Samuel 11-12), the foreign wives that turned Solomon away from God (1 King 11:4). These leaders were all strong men that gave in to sexual temptation. (Prov 7:26)

Because It doesn’t matter how strong you are or how self-disciplined you are. The secret to overcoming sexual sin is not you. It’s not being strong enough. It’s not having enough self-discipline. The Secret to overcoming sexual sin is knowing Him.” @reslife_youth #oneheart  #oneheartconfrence #acrossmyheart #reclaimingpurity #sexualtemptation #overcome #overcomingsin #metoo #churchtoo

There are those days where you realize, wow, I've changed. The days when you're not quite sure about much except for how grateful you are for everything that has brought you to the point that you're at. I stood up yesterday at the memorial in from of 250-300 ppl and shared from my heart. I had a previous coworker come up and say wow, you never would have done that a year or two ago and I almost got defensive... But then you realize that they are 150% right, no way in heck would I have. I might have felt like I had stuff to say but I never would have had the confidence to do so (that was part of it, he brought toastmasters to the firm and it's helped immensely!), but still, from where I was, how I was, my thought processes, my mental health... to who I am today... Don't ever think that you don't have a choice to change. Every second is a new opportunity to say you know what? F this. It's been quite the journey to get here, but I'm ready for the good, I'm ready for more growth, I'm ready for what this life wants to test me with next. Stronger every single day.

Meet Erin Sternstein (She/her/hers)! Erin is a writer, poet, solo theater performer, yoga teacher and activist. She debuted her one-woman show #metoo at the Whitefire Theatre’s SOLOFEST in 2018, and then went on to showcase it at the Hollywood Fringe Festival in June of 2018. #metoo is a 30 character comedic true story about sexual assault, abortion, and domestic violence. Erin was on the Oakland Slam Poetry Team in 2016, and is the author of “Your Pussy  is Magic,” a collection of poetry. She is a graduate of NYU’s Tisch School of the Arts and UCB Improv. ig: erin_is_on_ig #Queenfest2019

Often, our most delectably potent #powderpuffs come from roots, twigs + mushies. .
Such as this fine blend.
.
Today, 7 sisters asked to join in union for a very special #yonipowder . .
The goal? juicin’ up the wombspace- the lining of all our layers of tissues- from the lovely labia to the most mysterious of #spots for sensual pleasure all the way around. 😉
.
I will try to put the recipe + perhaps a video too! in our next email if I can just muster the desire to get onto my computer this fine rainy day before heading outside to play. 😍
.
I also just noticed that how I played with the filters on the picture, makes this counter of herbals look dirty. Interesting. And instead of taking it down and redoing it, I’ve decided...hey, what’s a lil dirt gonna hurt? Truly the counter is a clean one, but I can often get so caught up in “clean” and “perfect” that I miss the point, constrict the joy and forget to love the mess that life really is. So. To honor imperfection and choose dirt and mess, I’m just going to head outside. Happy Saturday. I hope it is full of perfectly imperfect joyful inspirations. 😉

”You will never know the impact your story will have, until you share and give it away.” My page will not contain photos of my children, myself, homestyle, clothes, or anything else- that in my experience, gain the most attention and followers. I gave up all of my personal social media to focus in on sharing my story when I discovered my 3.5yo child was being sexually abused by a family member. If I can be of service, contribute, or make a difference to a single human being, that is enough for me. Whether I have 10, 24, or more followers, as long as I have access to helping someone out there, nothing else matters. .
Simmm! Lógico que pode, principalmente se você criar “conexão” entre as peças.
.
No meu exemplo de hoje, a blusa de seda levemente dourada tem conexão com a estampa da saia e o sapato o mesmo tom da blusa. .
Esse é um dos truques de styling que ajuda a alongar a silhueta, mesmo usando peças que não são a “melhor opção” para seu tipo de corpo e altura.
.
Não precisa deixar de usar uma peça de roupa só porque disseram que não te favorece 😉
.

Today @abuseneverbecomesus spoke at "Vizhippu: Love, Power, and Relationships" - a conference which aimed to raise awareness about gender-based violence in the Tamil community. We spoke about Childhood Sexual Abuse. Very happy to have been invited to speak, and many people connected with the team after.  The conference was sponsored/funded by the City of Toronto and Family Services Toronto. Other topics included Gender-based violence in respect to the LGBTQ+ identifying persons, elderly population, newcomers,  persons with disabilities, legality, etc. It was great to see the reception from the community, nd to see so many people come out to an event which focused on gender-based violence. #socialcause #socialchange #childhoodsexualabuse #rights #metoo
